turn.2: Tangaroasaurus  Tangaroasaurus is an extinct genus of squalodontid whale from the Miocene of New Zealand.
turn.4: It contains a single species, Tangaroasaurus kakanuiensis.
turn.6: Similar to "Basilosaurus" and its close relative "Squalodon", it was originally thought to be a species of marine reptile.
turn.7: Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?
turn.8: Parts of the Holotype are presumably lost.
turn.10: Tagaroasaurus name comes from the Maori word for god of the water, while the suffix saurus comes from the latin word for reptile, the group that Tangaroasaurus was originally placed in.
turn.12: The type fossil was found in a grey clay deposit at All Day Bay and consists of a jaw bearing a few teeth, measuring 5 cm each.
